      "beat_id": "YTV01",
      "act": "VERDICT",
      "engine": "kokoro",
      "voice": "am_onyx",
      "lead_silence_s": 0.5,
      "narration_text": "Let's recap with Claude. Human labeling at scale is expensive, inconsistent, and produces pattern-matching rather than understanding of why something is harmful. Constitutional AI writes sixteen principles, then has Claude critique each harmful response against one and revise it. Three iterations of self-revision become the training data, yielding a model as harmless as the human-feedback version. The caveat stands: humans still write the constitution, so its values are made explicit and scalable, not removed.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "remotion",
        "motion": "hold",
        "remotion": {
          "pattern": "ClaudeVerdictArtifact",
          "provenance": "proven-core/ClaudeVerdictArtifact",
