    {
      "beat_id": "B00",
      "act": "cold open",
      "scene": "ClaudeComposerAsk",
      "narration_text": "The critique-then-revise loop across three iterations, turning self-revised responses into training data, is the mechanism I want to try on paper. Can you help me (1) draft two or three constitutional principles specific enough to actually drive a revision, (2) walk one harmful response through critique, revision, and a second pass so I see it get cleaner, and (3) explain why the resulting model matches human-feedback harmlessness while the caveat, that humans still wrote the constitution, remains true?",
      "voice": "am_onyx",
      "engine": "kokoro",
      "estimated_duration_s": 16.5,
      "actual_duration_s": 14.14,
