    {
      "beat_id": "B01",
      "act": "the problem with human labeling",
      "scene": "B01_LabelingProblem",
      "narration_text": "Human labeling at scale has three problems: it is expensive, it is inconsistent across annotators, and it produces a model that mimics what annotators dislike rather than one that understands why something is harmful. You get pattern-matching, not reasoning.",
      "voice": "am_onyx",
      "engine": "kokoro",
      "estimated_duration_s": 17.7,
      "actual_duration_s": 15.0,
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B01.mp3",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "graphic": {
          "engine": "manim",
          "manim": "B01_LabelingProblem",
          "production_viz": "Three boxes: Expensive / Inconsistent / Pattern-matching — each with a cost/problem annotation"
        }
      },
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B01.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-16T23:59:43"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B02",
      "act": "the critique-revision loop",
      "scene": "B02_CritiqueLoop",
      "narration_text": "Constitutional AI replaces most of that labeling. Write sixteen principles — the constitution. Then, for each harmful response, run this loop: Claude critiques the response against a principle, then revises it. The revised response is cleaner. Run it again. Three iterations. The self-revised responses become the training data.",
      "voice": "am_onyx",
      "engine": "kokoro",
      "estimated_duration_s": 21.2,
      "actual_duration_s": 18.01,
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B02.mp3",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "graphic": {
          "engine": "manim",
          "manim": "B02_CritiqueLoop",
          "production_viz": "Animated feedback loop: Harmful response -> Critique -> Revision -> Repeat x3. Quality bar improves each cycle."
        }
      },
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B02.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-16T23:59:43"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B03",
      "act": "RLAIF result",
      "scene": "B03_RLAIFResult",
      "narration_text": "The resulting model — trained on AI-generated preference data, not human labels — scores as harmless as the human-feedback model. On helpfulness, it scores slightly better. The caveat: the constitution is still written by humans. You have not removed human values from the loop. You have made them more explicit and made them scale.",
      "voice": "am_onyx",
      "engine": "kokoro",
      "estimated_duration_s": 21.2,
      "actual_duration_s": 17.41,
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B03.mp3",
